## 🌐 Deployment

- **Frontend:** Deploy to [Netlify](https://app.netlify.com/) (connect your GitHub repo, set environment variables in dashboard).
- **Backend:** Deploy to your preferred Node.js hosting (Heroku, Render, etc.).
- **Android App:** Build and distribute via Android Studio.

---

## 🛡️ Security

- **Sensitive data** (API keys, secrets) are stored in `.env` and **never committed to GitHub**.
- For deployment, set environment variables in your hosting provider’s dashboard.

---

## 📁 Key Files & Directories

- `src/` – React app source code
- `server.js` – Express backend entry point
- `app/` – Android app source
- `.env` – Environment variables (not committed)
- `.gitignore` – Ensures secrets and build files are not tracked

